data.title: American Ladder Institute plans to mark 10th year of National Ladder Safety Month in 2026, reducing ladder injuries and fatalities.
data.description: In Cleveland, the American Ladder Institute (ALI) is preparing to mark a decade of promoting safer climbing with the upcoming 10th anniversary of National Ladder Safety Month in 2026. This initiative, launched in 2016, is the sole program in the U.S. focused solely on advocating for safe ladder practices in both work environments and homes. Over the years, it has assisted millions of entities and people in decreasing ladder-related dangers, accidents, and deaths by providing education, training, and support. This milestone celebration signifies significant progress in enhancing ladder safety nationally.

data.title: Holiday shoppers increasingly rely on AI for deals and gift ideas, but retailers lacking transparency with only 51% disclosing AI usage. 80% of retailers using AI expect higher holiday sales and 79% foresee boosted customer loyalty.
data.description: A recent survey revealed that 75% of consumers plan to use AI for finding deals, and 67% for gift ideas during the holiday season, marking AI as a crucial tool for holiday shopping. However, while 84% of consumers want to be informed about AI usage, only 51% of retailers disclose their AI implementation. Among AI-using retailers, 80% anticipate higher holiday sales and 79% expect greater customer loyalty. The report emphasizes the need for retailers to balance AI technology with ethics to maintain customer trust. 69% of consumers believe AI support will make them happier, and 70% will be less stressed during the holidays. The full story is available on Benzinga.com.
